text="A comonad for Grothendieck fibrations">A comonad for Grothendieck fibrations</fr:title><fr:taxon>Reference</fr:taxon><fr:meta
name="doi">10.48550/arXiv.2305.01474</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We study the 2-category theory of Grothendieck fibrations in the 2-category of functors <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Cat}^{\to }]]></fr:tex>. After redrawing a few general results in that context, we show that fibrations over a given base are pseudo-coalgebras for a 2-comonad on  <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathbf {Cat}}_{/B}]]></fr:tex>. We use that result to explain how an arbitrary fibration is equivalent to one with a splitting.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>